<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>BlogSpace - All Blogs</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="bg-mesh"></div>
    
    <div class="container">
        <nav>
            <a href="/" class="logo">BlogSpace</a>
            <div class="nav-links">
                <a href="/compose">Write a Blog</a>
                <!-- Optional logic for auth states -->
            </div>
        </nav>

        <div class="fade-in" style="margin-top: 3rem;">
            <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: flex-end; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
                <div>
                    <h2>Latest Articles</h2>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">Discover stories, thinking, and expertise.</p>
                </div>
                <a href="/compose" class="btn btn-primary">Compose</a>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-panel" style="padding: 2rem;">
                
                <!-- This section is meant for EJS For Loop -->
                <!-- Example static blog preview card 1 -->
                <div class="blog-card">
                    <h3>The Art of Glassmorphism in Modern Web Design</h3>
                    <div class="meta">By John Doe • Oct 24, 2026</div>
                    <p>Glassmorphism represents an evolution in UI design, blending semi-transparent backgrounds with vibrant colors to create depth and visual hierarchy. In this post, we explore how to effectively use blurred elements...</p>
                    <a href="/posts/sample-1" class="btn btn-outline" style="padding: 0.5rem 1rem; font-size: 0.9rem;">Read More</a>
                </div>

                <!-- Example static blog preview card 2 -->
                <div class="blog-card">
                    <h3>Getting Started with Express and EJS</h3>
                    <div class="meta">By Jane Smith • Oct 22, 2026</div>
                    <p>Building dynamic web applications requires a solid understanding of templating engines. EJS provides a simple yet powerful syntax for weaving JavaScript logic directly into your HTML markup...</p>
                    <a href="/posts/sample-2" class="btn btn-outline" style="padding: 0.5rem 1rem; font-size: 0.9rem;">Read More</a>
                </div>

                <!-- Replace the above with EJS loop something like:
                <% posts.forEach(function(post){ %>
                    <div class="blog-card">
                        <h3><%= post.title %></h3>
                        <p><%= post.content.substring(0, 150) + "..." %></p>
                        <a href="/posts/<%= post._id %>" class="btn btn-outline">Read More</a>
                    </div>
                <% }) %>
                -->

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
